@xryz wrote:

ok i was reading on pack200 b/c i remembered that jagex uses it and i tried to un arcive one of thepack files with this program.
rsunpacker.java : [code]import java.io.File;
import java.io.FileOutputStream;
import java.io.IOException;
import java.util.jar.JarOutputStream;
import java.util.jar.Pack200;
import java.util.jar.Pack200.*;

public class rsunpacker {

public static void main(String args[]) {
try {
rsunpacker();
} catch (IOException e) {
// TODO Auto-generated catch block
e.printStackTrace();
}
}

public static void rsunpacker() throws IOException {
try {
File f = new File("./runescape.pack");
FileOutputStream fostream = new FileOutputStream("./runescape.jar");
JarOutputStream jostream = new JarOutputStream(fostream);
Unpacker unpacker = Pack200.newUnpacker();
// Call the unpacker
unpacker.unpack(f, jostream);
// Must explicitly close the output.
jostream.close();
} catch (IOException ioe) {
ioe.printStackTrace();
}
}
}[/code] it comes up with this error :
